\#\# Section 1: Business Model Summary (2 Paragraphs)

\*\*Paragraph 1: Identity & Scale Statement\*\*  
Synthesize Market Footprint positioning \+ Economic Foundation scale \+ Revenue Model client profile \+ Delivery Architecture team structure into complete business model characterization.

Structure: "You're operating a \[scale descriptor\] \[agency type\] serving \[client tier/industry context\] through a \[pricing model descriptor\] model. Your \[team size\]-person team delivers on a \[MRR/project split\] with \[ACV descriptor\] average client value."

Example: "You're operating a $1.2M specialist agency serving mid-market clients across regulated industries through a relationship-driven retainer model. Your 24-person generalist team delivers on a 60/40 retainer-project split with $2,857 average client value."

\*\*Paragraph 2: Structural Reality Statement\*\*  
Introduce the key cross-dimensional dynamic that defines strategic position. Reference the dominant Critical Insight theme.

Structure: "At \[key metric\] with \[key metric\] and \[key metric\], you're running a \[characterization of structural dynamic\]. \[What this creates/requires\]."

Example: "At 3% monthly churn with $2,857 ACV and 0.4-month cash runway, you're running a relationship-intensive operation where retention and key account stewardship are structural imperatives. The combination of replacement pressure and thin liquidity creates tight operational constraints despite strong 32% profitability."

\*\*Length:\*\* \~150 words total

